                            <h1>Attitude Selection</h1>
                            <div class="divider"></div>
                            <p>This section helps you find the appropriate attitude control subsystem for your CubeSat. The page asks for the altitude of your science orbit (at periapsis, if you have an elliptical orbit), along with the maximum spatial resolution that you need for measurment. From these inputs, we will calculate your angle of knowledge and angle of control (generally, the angle of knowledge needs to be 10 times better than the angle of control). <!-- Angle of Knowledge is calculated as: arctan(resolution/(1000*attitude)). The angle is represented in degrees. Angle of control is calculated as 10x(Calculated Angle of Knowledge). Instruments are displayed if their angle of precision is greater than or equal to the calculated angle of knowledge. -->We will display all subsystems that have an angle of precision lesser than or equal to the calculated angle of knowledge.</p>
                            <!-- <h3>What to Do: </h3>
                            <h4>On this page please input the altitude at which you would like to take measurements, and the maximum spatial resolution of your instrument. With this information we will calculate the required angle of knowledge and angle of control for your mission. This will allow us to search for acceptable attitude control systems.</h4> -->
                        </div>
                    </div>
