                            <h1>Communication Selection</h1>
                            <div class="divider"></div>
                            <p>This section will let you choose an antenna, receiver, and ground station from a selected band. We currently have parts for the VHF, UVF, S, and X band, which ranges from .3 GHz to 12 GHz. Once the antenna, receiver, and ground station are chosen for an associated band, we will calculate a free-path space loss term, a receive power term, a signal to noise ratio, and a maximum bit rate achievable by the chosen subsystem using known values of the chosen parts (such as EIRP, gain, frequency, bandwidth, and transmit power).</p> 
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-lg-2">
                        <div class="row" style="height: 200px">
                        </div>
